    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>PETROBRAS FACES FINES</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Jennifer L. Rich</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Rich, Jennifer L</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Brazil's state-owned oil company Petrobras could be fined up to $84 million after oil spill on July 16 polluted river in southern state of Parana; graph (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Brazil's state-owned oil company, Petrobras, could be fined up to $84 million after an oil spill on Sunday polluted a river in the southern state of Parana. The 25,000-barrel spill came a week after the government had put about $5 billion of the company's voting shares up for sale to the Brazilian public. Investors have until the end of July to place their orders. The remaining shares will be sold to international investors. Last year, Petrobras was fined $29 million for a spill in Guanabara Bay in Rio de Janeiro.</p>
        <p>Jennifer L. Rich (NYT)</p>
      </block>
